    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-10-22T19:46:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-10-22T19:46:00-05:00" n="1265"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1265">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.00/10–2254: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State, at Paris</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d1265fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_YKT1"
                            >Young</persName> of <gloss target="#t_PSA1">PSA</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>
                            <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-10-22T19:46:00-05:00"
                            >October 22, 1954—7:46 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Tedul1">Tedul</gloss> 13. Personal for Secretary. From Acting
                    Secretary. I believe two subsequent telegrams on Viet-Nam<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d1265fn2">See <gloss target="#t_Tedul1">Tedul</gloss> 14 (1678 to
                        Saigon), <ref target="#d1266">
                            <hi rend="italic">infra</hi>
                        </ref>, and telegram 1679 to Saigon (<gloss target="#t_Tedul1">Tedul</gloss>
                        15), <ref target="#pg_2161">p. 2161</ref>.</note> situation faithfully
                    reflect your thinking. Telegram of instructions to <persName corresp="#p_HDR1"
                        >Heath</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_ODLGJW1">O’Daniel</persName> on
                    starting limited <gloss target="#t_MAAG1">MAAG</gloss> program represents
                    intensive week of work and debate in <gloss target="#t_OCB1">OCB</gloss> finally
                    culminating in Defense and <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> acceptance. This
                    is significant step. Whole matter presented to President this morning at <gloss
                        target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss>.<note n="3" xml:id="d1265fn3">See extracts from
                        the memorandum of discussion at the 218th Meeting of the National Security
                        Council, Oct. 22, <ref target="#d1264">
                            <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> He approved general lines of action detailed by <gloss
                        target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> and State in that telegram. We now have
                    something concrete to work with. It carries risk but without some move we would
                    remain on dead center.</p>
                <p>Suggest if possible you inform Deputy Defense Secretary <persName
                        corresp="#p_ARB1">Anderson</persName> of this message and instructions to
                        <persName corresp="#p_HDR1">Heath</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_ODLGJW1">O’Daniel</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HHJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hoover</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
